tree on my campus.

05:20.885 --> 05:24.846
Oh, I'm sorry, it's a little too
graphic?

05:24.889 --> 05:27.283
I was just wondering if you guys
had heard anything about that.

05:27.327 --> 05:32.767
Yo any of you guys hear about a
rope hanging from a tree?

05:32.810 --> 05:35.160
Alexander you hear about this?

05:35.204 --> 05:43.299
Sorry man. Wish I
could help.

05:43.343 --> 05:49.436
You think you're safe here with
your little Backstreet Boys?

05:49.479 --> 05:53.527
You will always have to answer
to somebody. Bitch.

06:01.143 --> 06:02.579
SAM:
Aw shit!

06:12.197 --> 06:13.721
KEVIN:
Take it easy guys.

06:30.433 --> 06:32.261
VALARIE:
A bit more slack.

06:32.304 --> 06:33.567
[cell phone beeps]

06:34.568 --> 06:36.004
A little bit more.

06:36.047 --> 06:37.527
Hazem, you're playing with
your phone again!

06:37.571 --> 06:38.833
HAZEM:
I'm not playing with
anything!

06:38.876 --> 06:46.971
You have my life in your
hands. More slack.

06:47.015 --> 06:53.369
A bit more slack. More.

06:53.413 --> 06:56.546
Sorry about that pumpkin. It's
my phone, you know?

06:56.590 --> 06:57.765
I'm going to kill you!

06:57.808 --> 06:59.636
Who's going to give you
more slack?

06:59.680 --> 07:00.811
Just put me down.

07:00.855 --> 07:04.641
HAZEM [OS]:
Okay.

07:04.685 --> 07:06.948
[LAUGHTER]

07:06.991 --> 07:08.384
VALERIE [OS]:
Why are you so stubborn?

07:08.428 --> 07:10.952
HAZEM [OS]:
Stop forcing me to do
something.

07:10.995 --> 07:12.083
VALERIE [OS]:
I'm just suggesting.

07:12.127 --> 07:13.563
HAZEM [OS]:
Okay fine, so suggest.

07:13.607 --> 07:14.651
The blue button down.

07:14.695 --> 07:16.000
Oh anything but the blue button
down.

07:16.044 --> 07:16.871
You gotta look nice.

07:16.914 --> 07:18.089
You don't think I look nice?

07:18.133 --> 07:19.308
I think you look nice

07:19.351 --> 07:20.918
But I want my parents to think
you look nice.

07:20.962 --> 07:22.790
And why would I care what your
parents think?

07:22.833 --> 07:23.834
Because they're your future
in-laws.

07:23.878 --> 07:25.357
My future what?

07:25.401 --> 07:26.881
You're going to meet my parents

07:26.924 --> 07:28.491
and you're going to wear the
blue button down.

07:28.535 --> 07:29.449
I'll wear this shirt. How about
that?

07:29.492 --> 07:30.667
I don't like that shirt.

07:30.711 --> 07:32.234
You don't like this shirt. Are
you serious?

07:32.277 --> 07:34.454
Do you know what kind of
material this is?

07:34.497 --> 07:35.846
This is husband
material.

07:35.890 --> 07:36.543
Oh you're so-

07:36.586 --> 07:37.805
Hey Bobby! Tonight!

07:37.848 --> 07:39.589
BOBBY:
Tomorrow.

07:39.633 --> 07:41.243
- Tomorrow.
- Not tomorrow!

07:41.286 --> 07:44.246
Not tomorrow! Tonight. Just
later. Okay?

07:44.289 --> 07:48.163
Don't talk politics okay?
Especially not with my dad.

07:48.206 --> 07:50.513
Mmmm you think I'm going to
insult him or something?

07:50.557 --> 07:52.080
Oh let's see how do I say this?

07:52.123 --> 07:56.127
You're not exactly the best at
being politically correct.

07:56.171 --> 07:59.130
Well, we're not all poli-sci
majors are we?

07:59.174 --> 08:01.045
That's right. Dean's list baby.

08:01.089 --> 08:02.612
Yeah dean's list.

08:02.656 --> 08:04.875
Which reminds me, I'm taking you
next week to go register.

08:04.919 --> 08:09.010
Yeah, about that. No. I'm not
gonna vote, okay?

08:09.053 --> 08:10.446
We're just gonna register.

08:10.490 --> 08:13.493
I'm not gonna vote unless I get
the free ice cream.

08:18.106 --> 08:19.629
Okay. Convince
me.

08:19.673 --> 08:22.676
Okay. It is said that a weakened
sense of responsibility...

08:22.719 --> 08:25.592
does not actually weaken the
fact of responsibility.

08:25.635 --> 08:28.464
Okay...Huh?

08:28.508 --> 08:30.988
Are you seriously not voting?

08:31.032 --> 08:33.164
Look I just don't wanna watch
two rich guys debate

08:33.207 --> 08:35.253
and then jump on
a bandwagon.

08:35.297 --> 08:37.559
Smart people don't do
that.

08:37.604 --> 08:40.083
Oh Great. So when all the smart
people think like you...

08:40.128 --> 08:44.436
who does that leave to vote?

08:44.480 --> 08:46.351
You.

08:46.395 --> 08:48.528
I can't vote for all of us.

08:48.571 --> 08:52.532
Aw sure you can. Ow!

08:53.794 --> 08:56.144
GARRET:
Okay, you keep this in your
fridge to keep your food fresh.

08:56.187 --> 08:57.972
BRAD:
It makes things rise when
you bake.

08:58.015 --> 09:02.498
MEGAN:
Baking soda. Um, pure sodium
bi-carbonate. Na H CO3.

09:02.542 --> 09:07.068
Nice.

09:07.111 --> 09:08.548
Okay, this is an easy one.

09:08.591 --> 09:11.551
You use it to sweeten your
drinks. You put it in tea.

09:11.594 --> 09:14.292
Honey. But that's not a
compound. So--

09:14.336 --> 09:15.946
Honey? How old are you?

09:15.990 --> 09:17.339
That's what I put in my tea.

09:17.382 --> 09:20.124
Alright what does everyone else
in the world use?

09:20.168 --> 09:22.083
How you get so fly.

09:22.126 --> 09:23.606
Oh jesus. Sugar.

09:23.650 --> 09:24.172
BRAD [OS]:
There ya go.

09:24.215 --> 09:27.044
Uh. C12 H22 O11

09:27.088 --> 09:28.002
You got it.

09:28.045 --> 09:31.527
Nice. Honey? Good Lord man!

09:31.571 --> 09:33.137
GARRET [OS]:
Oh, sorry that's
mine.

09:33.181 --> 09:34.574
Yo what is this?

09:34.617 --> 09:35.749
Are you competing for that?

09:35.792 --> 09:38.099
Uh, I'm not competing. I'm gonna
get it.

09:38.142 --> 09:40.928
That's awesome. That's a ton of
money.

09:40.971 --> 09:42.103
And if you win, you can always
use it to--

09:42.146 --> 09:44.801
Dude! Thirty thousand dollars?

09:44.845 --> 09:48.109
Please help yourself to the
middle of my sentence!

09:48.152 --> 09:50.067
Well you know my dad's been
looking for a job...

09:50.111 --> 09:52.809
for a couple of months and I
thought, you know,

09:52.853 --> 09:56.639
this might help him out a bit.
So, you know we'll see.

09:56.683 --> 09:58.467
That's awesome.

09:58.510 --> 10:01.731
CASHIER:
Sir. It is declined. I have
other customers to help out.

10:01.775 --> 10:04.168
CUSTOMER:
I told you. If it don't work, I
can get you another one.

10:04.212 --> 10:05.735
I can't accept any other payment
sir,

10:05.779 --> 10:07.781
I'm going to have to ask you
to step aside.

10:07.824 --> 10:10.087
Are you kidding me? I go to
school here.

10:10.131 --> 10:11.436
Man, just hold on a
second.

10:11.480 --> 10:13.308
Woah, hey man get your hand out
of your pocket.

10:13.351 --> 10:17.181
RACIST:
Hey! You heard the guy. Let's
keep it moving a little bit huh?

10:17.225 --> 10:20.750
Wha-pish!

10:20.794 --> 10:22.143
What'd you say?

10:22.186 --> 10:24.232
I said why don't you take your
stolen credit cards...

10:24.275 --> 10:27.365
and go to the fried chicken
place down the street, alright?

10:27.409 --> 10:29.324
So what's up man, you got a
problem with me or what?

10:29.367 --> 10:31.152
Hey, hey, let me take care of
this for you alright.

10:31.195 --> 10:32.544
How much was it?

10:32.588 --> 10:33.458
CASHIER:
Look man I don't need
this right now.

10:33.502 --> 10:34.285
No it's fine. I got it.

10:34.329 --> 10:36.200
What's your problem man?

10:36.244 --> 10:38.333
Out of my way nig-nog okay?
Alright?

10:38.725 --> 10:39.639
[punch]

10:42.076 --> 10:44.426
CAHSIER [OS]:
You know what?
Alright alright!

10:44.469 --> 10:46.341
Get out. All of you! You too.
Now! Get out.

10:46.384 --> 10:48.560
You three too. Leave. Now get
out.

10:48.604 --> 10:50.214
Are you serious?

10:50.258 --> 10:50.780
GARETT [OS]:
I was just helping him out man.

10:50.824 --> 10:51.999
Are you okay?

10:52.042 --> 10:53.174
CASHIER [OS]:
Leave!
- Yeah, I'm fine.

10:53.217 --> 10:55.437
Jesus.

11:01.748 --> 11:03.619
GARRET:
Hey. What's up?

11:03.663 --> 11:07.101
ALEXANDER:
What's up? Fifteen pages on the
elasticity of macro-economics.

11:07.144 --> 11:08.711
We were supposed to meet in the
grad library.

11:08.755 --> 11:11.235
Dude. I am so sorry, you wanna
come in?

11:13.281 --> 11:15.239
ASSISTANT [OS]:
Miss Torrance? Thank you for
waiting.

11:15.283 --> 11:17.415
Dean Marison will see you
now.

11:17.459 --> 11:19.069
ROSE:
Thank you so much for meeting
with me Dean.

11:19.113 --> 11:20.418
I know that you're extremely
busy.

11:20.462 --> 11:22.856
DEAN:
Oh not at all. This is why I'm
here.

11:22.899 --> 11:26.250
Yes sir. Um, I guess the problem
now is that students are feeling

11:26.294 --> 11:28.818
offended by the events that
are happening on campus,

11:28.862 --> 11:30.211
especially the noose hanging

11:30.254 --> 11:33.388
Valerie. Make sure you get all
this.

11:33.431 --> 11:37.218
Listen miss Torrance, the
situation is bad.

11:37.261 --> 11:40.264
It's bad for the students. It's
bad for the university.

11:40.308 --> 11:41.613
It's bad for everyone.

11:41.657 --> 11:43.920
I want you to know that the
administration...

11:43.964 --> 11:47.054
and myself deeply
condemn these actions.

11:47.097 --> 11:48.620
I mean that's why we're here!

11:48.664 --> 11:52.059
To teach people and help them
grow out of their ignorance.

11:52.102 --> 11:55.715
That's the role we play as
educators.

12:00.981 --> 12:02.852
GARRET:
Okay what the hell does this
mean?

12:02.896 --> 12:06.073
"Obama's presidency would be the
camel's nose."

12:06.116 --> 12:07.378
ALEXANDER:
What are you reading?

12:07.422 --> 12:11.339
It's my homepage. It's the news
page.

12:11.382 --> 12:15.430
An old Arabian proverb
states if...

12:15.473 --> 12:17.475
the camels nose enters the
tent...

12:17.519 --> 12:19.477
his body will soon follow.

12:19.521 --> 12:22.742
I feel like I should be
offended by something here.

12:22.785 --> 12:23.917
What's her name?

12:23.960 --> 12:26.746
Buggle. Yo, watch it, she's
slippery.

12:26.789 --> 12:29.313
You know the French eat frogs
like this.

12:29.357 --> 12:31.881
Yeah?

12:31.925 --> 12:35.189
Oh yeah. Boiled frog legs.

12:35.232 --> 12:37.974
Miss Buggle would be a real
delicacy over there.

12:38.018 --> 12:41.151
Sounds gross. And painful.

12:41.195 --> 12:45.416
Some French cooks found that if
you put a frog in water,

12:45.460 --> 12:47.636
It'll just sit there and enjoy
the drink.

12:47.679 --> 12:51.335
But if you start slowly turning
up the heat,

12:51.379 --> 12:52.510
the frog will fall
asleep.

12:52.554 --> 12:54.425
Turn up the heat
a little more,

12:54.469 --> 12:56.819
it'll fall into a
deeper sleep.

12:56.863 --> 13:01.171
Eventually the water's boiling,
and Miss Buggle is dead.

13:01.215 --> 13:04.435
That's how you go from a
live frog to a meal.

13:04.479 --> 13:07.656
That's what they mean by the
camel's nose.

13:07.699 --> 13:11.878
They're wondering how this guy
whose ancestors came over...

13:11.921 --> 13:13.488
to this country chained up on a
boat...

13:13.531 --> 13:17.709
ends up running for
president.

13:17.753 --> 13:21.844
You gonna take that?

13:21.888 --> 13:24.760
No, that's fine.

13:24.804 --> 13:27.154
It's 8:30. Let's get started on
this paper.

13:28.372 --> 13:34.422
ROSE:
Dean. Off the record, are we
just going to let these guys go?

13:34.465 --> 13:39.383
DEAN:
Off the record, Rose, let who
go? We don't know who did this.

13:39.427 --> 13:40.645
Of course, we know who did this.

13:40.689 --> 13:43.387
You and I both know exactly who
did this.

13:43.431 --> 13:45.868
Are you suggesting the Kappa
House is responsible?

13:45.912 --> 13:46.826
So you do know.

13:46.869 --> 13:48.349
What I know, Rose,

13:48.392 --> 13:50.960
is that college students love
spreading rumors.

13:51.004 --> 13:53.354
ROSE [OS]:
These are not rumors
dean Marison.

13:53.397 --> 13:55.704
The Kappa House has a history of
racism...

13:55.747 --> 13:57.749
that everyone seems to
acknowledge except...

13:57.793 --> 13:59.316
this administration.

13:59.360 --> 14:03.364
As a results of recent tensions,
we have instated mandatory

14:03.407 --> 14:06.193
diversity training for all
campus organizations.

14:06.236 --> 14:07.803
And that is gonna do what
exactly?

14:07.847 --> 14:10.675
Valerie, would you please?

14:10.719 --> 14:12.373
VALERIE:
The administration cannot charge
a group of students...

14:12.416 --> 14:14.897
with a hate crime without
substantial evidence.

14:14.941 --> 14:16.507
Oh, she's good.

14:16.551 --> 14:20.294
Dean. This is a threat to every
black student on this campus.

14:20.337 --> 14:21.512
DEAN [OS]:
I can understand that,
Miss Torrance.

14:21.556 --> 14:23.079
ROSE [OS]:
No I don't think you
do.

14:23.123 --> 14:25.908
We're going to explore every
possible means by which we can

14:25.952 --> 14:28.868
find out what happened. We'll
set up a safe space--

14:28.911 --> 14:30.478
With all due respect dean.

14:30.521 --> 14:33.611
There is a noose hanging from a
tree in your safe space.

14:33.655 --> 14:35.483
We don't need to explore what
happened.

14:35.526 --> 14:40.270
You and I know exactly what
happened and who made it happen.

14:40.314 --> 14:42.098
We can't know anyone's intention
Rose.

14:42.142 --> 14:44.535
It's not fair to misjudge
people...

14:44.579 --> 14:47.756
just as you wouldn't like
to be misjudged.

14:47.799 --> 14:50.933
I would think someone like
yourself would understand that.

14:50.977 --> 14:53.283
Dean. Do you want me to keep
typing?

14:53.327 --> 14:57.113
No. Thank you for your time.

14:57.157 --> 15:04.120
Miss Torrance. I want to assure
you there is no need to worry.

15:04.164 --> 15:06.470
This is an isolated incident.

15:12.085 --> 15:17.394
[soulful music]

15:31.713 --> 15:36.283
TREY:
Hey what'd he say? Rose, come on
what'd he say?

15:38.024 --> 15:41.331
You okay?

15:41.375 --> 15:42.506
Rose!

15:42.550 --> 15:43.943
ROSE:
One minute Trey.

15:47.729 --> 15:50.210
[sobs]

16:38.736 --> 16:41.174
DIMON [OS]:
Take a break. Take a break

16:48.485 --> 16:51.358
DIMON:
Time! Alright, we're gonna...

16:51.401 --> 16:52.837
work our inside
counter-punch drill.

16:52.881 --> 16:53.882
HAZEM:
Alright.

16:53.925 --> 16:55.188
If I throw my left hook too
wide,

16:55.231 --> 16:57.146
you shoot it straight
right down the middle.

16:57.190 --> 17:00.541
Got it.

17:00.584 --> 17:02.369
Oh okay. Nice, nice.

17:02.412 --> 17:03.761
Yeah money!

17:03.805 --> 17:07.852
Okay, alright. Now, when you
feed that right hand,

17:07.896 --> 17:09.854
you better be ready to defend
yourself, alright?

17:09.897 --> 17:13.728
Alright.

17:13.771 --> 17:15.164
BOTH:
Keep your hands up!

17:15.208 --> 17:16.644
I let you have that man.

17:16.686 --> 17:18.166
Yeah right.

17:18.211 --> 17:20.213
So how come your girl don't come
see you fight no more?

17:20.256 --> 17:22.606
Because I don't wanna embarrass
you like this every time.

17:22.650 --> 17:26.045
I know you got this ego thing
going man.

17:26.088 --> 17:28.612
In the ring, I want you
to be confident, not cocky.

17:28.656 --> 17:31.050
Cocky will get you killed.
Alright?

17:31.093 --> 17:32.573
You need to watch some Rocky or
something,

17:32.616 --> 17:33.400
and learn how to
coach!

17:33.443 --> 17:34.096
Rocky?

17:34.140 --> 17:35.402
Yeah.

17:35.445 --> 17:37.099
Man you leave the coaching to
me. I got this.

17:37.143 --> 17:39.536
You be ready to practice this
weekend and bring your A-game.

17:39.580 --> 17:40.885
HZEM [OS]:
It's the only game I
got man!

17:40.929 --> 17:43.714
DIMON [OS]:
Man what'd I just
say?

17:52.245 --> 17:55.117
ROSE:
I can't believe you talked
me into this.

17:55.161 --> 17:57.815
MALIK:
It is cold and wet out
here.

17:57.859 --> 18:00.905
TREY:
Yo, don't even worry about
it. Let's go.

18:00.949 --> 18:03.212
It's beautiful though.

18:03.256 --> 18:11.481
Yeah, it is.

18:11.525 --> 18:12.830
Yeah! Hey pass it here.

18:12.874 --> 18:14.310
TREY [OS]:
Hell no dude you ain't
touching this.

18:14.354 --> 18:16.617
First we're trespassing now, you
have a weapon.

18:16.660 --> 18:18.053
What are you
doing?

18:18.097 --> 18:22.623
Yo, Relax. It's not a weapon.
It's a baseball bat.

18:22.666 --> 18:24.277
MALIK [OS]:
What are you going to do with a
bat and a football anyway?

18:24.320 --> 18:26.583
KEVIN:
You poor ignorant souls.

18:26.627 --> 18:27.758
Batter up!

18:27.802 --> 18:30.109
Swing batter, batter, batter!

18:30.152 --> 18:31.762
ROSE [OS]:
Oh my goodness!

18:31.806 --> 18:36.158
That one's outta here folks! Get
money, get paid baby.

18:42.730 --> 18:47.256
It's okay, you can smile.

18:50.520 --> 18:53.262
ROSE [VO]:
When all the doors are closed,

18:53.306 --> 18:57.701
when you feel like you're
carrying the world on your back,

18:57.745 --> 19:00.182
it's easy to forget that you're
just a kid.

19:02.532 --> 19:04.839
VALERIE:
You know I almost drowned as a
little kid?

19:04.882 --> 19:08.277
HAZEML
Drowned? So I almost never
met you huh?

19:08.321 --> 19:10.714
Yeah. I almost died.

19:10.758 --> 19:18.069
Wow. Well did your life flash
before your eyes like they say?

19:18.113 --> 19:20.985
Actually, when something goes
wrong,

19:21.029 --> 19:23.336
your brain usually deals with it
by...

19:23.379 --> 19:24.989
trying to find a similar
situation.

19:25.033 --> 19:28.732
So, when you touch something
hot, what do you do?

19:28.776 --> 19:29.559
Pull my hand away.

19:29.603 --> 19:31.126
Right!

19:31.170 --> 19:32.301
Because your brain knows if you
don't pull your hand away,

19:32.345 --> 19:33.520
you're gonna get hurt.

19:33.563 --> 19:35.261
This happens in your brain all
the time...

19:35.304 --> 19:36.827
without you realizing it.

19:36.871 --> 19:38.220
You making all this up?

19:38.264 --> 19:40.962
No, I'm not. That's the case
when you're dying.

19:41.005 --> 19:43.312
Your brain knows that something
is very, very wrong.

19:43.356 --> 19:44.922
But your brain has never died
before.

19:44.966 --> 19:47.098
So it frantically searches
through all your memories

19:47.142 --> 19:49.144
until it can find a similar
situation...

19:49.188 --> 19:50.276
and hopefully save
you.

19:50.319 --> 19:51.015
But it can't.

19:51.059 --> 19:52.756
So before you die,

19:52.800 --> 19:56.760
your life actually does flash
before your eyes.

19:56.804 --> 19:59.415
Mmm, I think we should see other
people.

19:59.459 --> 20:02.113
Ha-ha. They don't teach you that
in med school, do they?

20:02.157 --> 20:03.419
Not exactly.

20:03.463 --> 20:05.378
I wonder what I'd see flashing
before my eyes.

20:05.421 --> 20:06.944
I don't know...

20:06.988 --> 20:09.860
but I'd rather look at life with
a more positive outlook.

20:09.904 --> 20:11.340
Yeah? How's that?

20:11.384 --> 20:14.952
Well. we can build our future
home, for example.

20:14.996 --> 20:16.040
Hmmm, Okay.

20:16.084 --> 20:16.911
You wanted palm trees out front,
right?

20:16.954 --> 20:19.130
Oh look! I found us a pet.

20:21.785 --> 20:22.395
The hell is that?

20:22.438 --> 20:23.265
It's a starfish.

20:23.309 --> 20:23.961
Yeah I can see that.

20:24.005 --> 20:25.398
Feel its skin.

20:25.441 --> 20:25.963
I don't wanna feel its skin. Get
that away from me.

20:26.007 --> 20:27.356
No, see this!

20:27.400 --> 20:28.749
No seriously. Valerie, I'm not
kidding, I'm serious.

20:28.792 --> 20:29.924
What are you scared?

20:29.967 --> 20:31.273
I'm not scared, it's got these
suction--

20:31.317 --> 20:32.535
No feel it!

20:32.579 --> 20:33.710
Valerie I'm not playing anymore.
Quit playing.

20:33.754 --> 20:36.844
Alright fine. You wanna handle
this like men?

20:36.887 --> 20:38.149
You wanna take this outside?

20:38.193 --> 20:39.412
We are outside.

20:39.455 --> 20:40.674
Well then we're efficient people
aren't we?

20:40.717 --> 20:42.153
Yes, we are effecient people!

20:42.197 --> 20:43.242
Okay.

20:43.285 --> 20:44.852
Alright, come on! Put your hands
up.

20:44.895 --> 20:46.462
I'm too fast for you, actually.
I'm so pretty, I'm so pretty.

20:46.506 --> 20:48.247
Float like a butterfly, sting
like a bee.

20:48.290 --> 20:49.987
I'm the pretty one in this
relationship, okay?

20:50.031 --> 20:52.294
Give me a break. Alright, give
me your left hook.

20:52.338 --> 20:54.470
This is my right hand. Here is a
left hook!

20:54.514 --> 20:56.211
Right hand?

20:56.255 --> 20:57.691
Fine! Give me a left hook! My
left!

20:57.734 --> 20:58.909
Whatever, my left!

20:59.214 --> 21:00.302
Okay, get ready.

21:00.346 --> 21:01.434
You can't punch me back!

21:01.477 --> 21:02.826
Why not?

21:02.870 --> 21:04.306
[giggles]

21:04.872 --> 21:06.961
You actually punched me!

21:07.004 --> 21:09.920
I'm not punching you
'cause you don't wanna get
punched!

21:17.450 --> 21:21.497
PLAYER 1:
I got you! Come on, come on!

21:21.541 --> 21:22.890
PLAYER 2:
Comin' up, comin' up!

21:27.764 --> 21:28.678
Come on! C'mon!

21:28.722 --> 21:31.333
TREY:
Yo! Hey! Hey!

21:35.076 --> 21:36.033
Look man!

21:36.077 --> 21:37.557
PLAYER 3:
What the hell, Trey!

21:37.600 --> 21:38.688
TREY [OS]:
I need all your attention. Get
up in here.

21:38.732 --> 21:39.385
PLAYER [OS]:
What's your problem man?

21:39.428 --> 21:40.516
This is my problem!

21:40.560 --> 21:41.865
PLAYER 4 [OS]:
What is this?

21:41.909 --> 21:44.477
"Compton Cookout. Join us for a
Nigga Night."

21:44.520 --> 21:46.479
GROUP:
What?
What the f--

21:46.522 --> 21:48.176
"In honor of celebrating our
black classmates,

21:48.219 --> 21:49.438
the Kappa House cordially
invites you...

21:49.482 --> 21:51.658
to its very first Compton
Cookout.

21:51.701 --> 21:53.703
All dudes should be rocking
jerseys,

21:53.747 --> 21:57.185
anything FUBU, Ecko, Jordans,
or Dunks.

21:57.228 --> 22:00.362
Ghetto chicks should have
gold teeth, start drama, and...

22:00.406 --> 22:02.016
wear cheap clothes. They look
and act like Shenaynay

22:02.059 --> 22:03.974
and speak loudly while rolling
their neck

22:04.018 --> 22:06.368
and waving their finger in your
face.

22:06.412 --> 22:09.023
The Kappa House is proud to
house this monstrosity

22:09.066 --> 22:10.590
so travel through the house

22:10.633 --> 22:12.896
and experience the various
elements of life in the ghetto.

22:12.940 --> 22:15.029
We'll be serving 40s, kegs
of dat purple drank,

22:15.072 --> 22:17.684
chicken, Kool-aid, and of course
watermelon.

22:17.727 --> 22:19.120
So come one, come
all.

22:19.163 --> 22:22.384
And join us for a party to be
remembered, or not."

22:22.428 --> 22:23.385
PLAYER 1 [OS]:
This is ridiculous.

22:23.429 --> 22:24.995
Can you believe this bullshit?

22:25.039 --> 22:27.389
Kappa House is off campus. They
can have any party they want.

22:27.433 --> 22:28.912
PLAYER 2 [OS]:
There's no way we can cancel it?

22:28.956 --> 22:29.783
TREY [OS]:
So we're just not going to do
anything?

22:31.306 --> 22:33.830
We're going.

22:33.874 --> 22:36.180
[group mutters in agreement]

22:46.277 --> 22:47.496
VALERIE:
What time is your fight
Saturday?

22:47.540 --> 22:48.584
HAZEM:
Six, I think.

22:48.628 --> 22:49.933
And you want me to come to this
one?

22:49.977 --> 22:50.717
Hell no.

22:50.760 --> 22:53.197
Fine, have it your way.

22:53.241 --> 22:55.025
I'll probably end up going to
that frat party then.

22:55.069 --> 22:57.071
Valerie why would you go to that
party?

22:57.114 --> 23:00.379
What, I can't handle going to a
party without you?

23:00.422 --> 23:02.381
It's messed up. It's a ghetto
themed party.

23:02.424 --> 23:04.034
No it's not. Where are you
getting this?

23:04.078 --> 23:05.427
Did you even see the fliers?

23:05.471 --> 23:08.778
What fliers? Okay never mind
let's just drop it.

23:08.822 --> 23:09.910
We need to get going anyway,

23:09.953 --> 23:13.000
my parents are waiting. 'Yalla
nimshy.'

23:15.481 --> 23:17.352
You know, when white girls try
to talk Arabic,

23:17.396 --> 23:20.442
usually it sounds pretty bad.
You though? it sucks.

23:20.486 --> 23:21.791
You are such a jerk!

23:21.835 --> 23:23.445
I know. You love me though,
right?

23:23.489 --> 23:24.403
Sure.

23:24.446 --> 23:26.274
Sure? I want you to say it.

23:26.317 --> 23:27.754
Yeah, I love you.

23:27.797 --> 23:31.366
Wow, I'm not convinced at all.
Say it and mean it!

23:31.410 --> 23:32.933
That's the best I got.

23:32.976 --> 23:35.501
Say it with some passion, like
it means something to you.

23:35.544 --> 23:36.980
No.

23:37.024 --> 23:37.981
Valerie, if you don't say it,
I'm gonna hurt myself.

23:38.025 --> 23:39.983
And how are you going to do
that?

23:40.027 --> 23:44.423
I'm gonna jump. And if I jump,
you're jumping with me.

23:44.466 --> 23:46.599
Oh, I would really like to see
that.

23:46.642 --> 23:47.426
You'd love to see me jump?

23:47.469 --> 23:48.427
Yeah.

23:48.470 --> 23:49.471
Last chance.

23:49.515 --> 23:50.907
Nope.

23:50.951 --> 23:52.953
My life's gonna flash before my
eyes. Last chance.

23:52.996 --> 23:53.823
Nope.

23:53.867 --> 23:55.651
Okay.

23:55.695 --> 23:56.391
Oh my Go-

23:56.435 --> 23:58.437
[doorbell rings]

23:58.480 --> 24:01.222
TIM:
Coming! Hello.

24:01.265 --> 24:02.266
Hey.

24:02.310 --> 24:03.311
VALERIE:
Hi.

24:03.354 --> 24:04.355
TIM:
The hell happened to you two?

24:04.399 --> 24:05.661
HAZEM:
There was a leak.

24:05.705 --> 24:08.011
There was a leak in the car?

24:08.055 --> 24:09.622
Yeah. Daddy this is Hazem.

24:09.665 --> 24:11.972
Good to finally meet you sir.

24:12.015 --> 24:14.104
Nice to meet you. Come on in.

24:14.148 --> 24:15.541
Thanks.

24:15.584 --> 24:17.586
This one will fit right into the
family photo album.

24:17.630 --> 24:18.718
Dad!

24:18.761 --> 24:19.675
Why don't you go upstairs,
Valerie,

24:19.719 --> 24:20.981
and get something dry to
wear.

24:21.024 --> 24:24.071
Maybe find something for
Khazem. Have a seat.

24:24.114 --> 24:26.639
Just don't sit on the sofa
please.

24:26.682 --> 24:32.601
So uh Khazem, that's an ethnic
name. isn't it?

24:32.645 --> 24:36.387
Uh, It depends on where you're
from I guess.

24:36.431 --> 24:37.519
Aren't you from the Middle East?

24:37.563 --> 24:41.175
I'm from Jersey. Hoboken.

24:41.218 --> 24:45.962
TIM [OS]:
You're from Jersey. Okay so...
Let's sit down somewhere.

24:46.006 --> 24:47.529
Maybe the dining room
table.

24:47.573 --> 24:48.225
Sure.

24:48.269 --> 24:49.531
So, uh...

24:49.575 --> 24:50.880
You have a beautiful home, by
the way.

24:50.924 --> 24:54.275
Thank you very much. I like to
keep it that way.

25:10.683 --> 25:14.556
SHEILA:
Oh my. Silence frightens
me.

25:14.600 --> 25:17.559
So Hazem, you haven't told us
what you've been studying.

25:17.603 --> 25:19.735
I'm a third year med student.

25:19.779 --> 25:21.476
3.8 GPA.

25:21.520 --> 25:25.001
Wow that's wonderful. Money is
always wonderful.

25:25.045 --> 25:28.178
That's why you're saying that
you hit the jackpot, Valerie?

25:28.222 --> 25:32.966
Dad! I never said that. I never
said that.

25:33.009 --> 25:34.315
TIM [OS]:
Well I'm saying it.

25:34.358 --> 25:37.405
So what's the medical field like
in your country?

25:37.448 --> 25:38.537
What happened?

25:38.580 --> 25:40.060
Valerie tells us you're from
Egypt.

25:40.103 --> 25:41.496
Egypt? You told me Jersey.

25:41.540 --> 25:43.063
His parents are from Egypt.

25:43.106 --> 25:44.891
Oh, so what? Are you going to
live in Egypt?

25:44.934 --> 25:48.503
No, Tim don't be silly. They're
staying right here of course.

25:48.547 --> 25:51.593
SHEILA [OS]:
Not that I don't like Egypt,
Hazem. .

25:51.637 --> 25:53.987
I've seen pictures of the
pyramids. Beautiful.

25:54.030 --> 25:55.728
What'd be so wrong with moving
to Egypt?

25:55.771 --> 25:57.338
I think it'd be exciting.

25:57.381 --> 26:00.646
But a person should live in the
best place they can afford.

26:00.689 --> 26:04.084
And you don't want to be around
all those diseases.

26:04.127 --> 26:05.651
That's frightening.

26:05.694 --> 26:09.045
Well, I think it's easy to judge
something from far away.

26:09.089 --> 26:11.308
Yeah, sure, but by the same
token,

26:11.352 --> 26:14.181
You wouldn't want to be living
in Compton, would you Kazem?

26:14.224 --> 26:16.705
Tim, you're being silly.
Compton.

26:16.749 --> 26:19.229
All those baggy pants and guns.

26:19.273 --> 26:22.058
You know just the sight of
guns--

26:22.102 --> 26:24.931
Frightens you. No, me too. I
agree.

26:24.974 --> 26:27.629
Dad, you grew up in Detroit
right?

26:27.673 --> 26:29.413
Warren. Yeah, a little city
called Warren.

26:29.457 --> 26:30.980
Yeah? What was that like?

26:31.024 --> 26:32.329
It was clean.

26:34.331 --> 26:35.158
[doorbell rings]

26:35.202 --> 26:36.682
SHEILA [OS]:
Who's that?

26:36.725 --> 26:38.379
No, wait a second. No, nobody
needs get up, I'll get it.

26:38.422 --> 26:39.902
Claire, eat your food.

26:41.512 --> 26:42.513
TIM [OS]:
Hey, Garret my son!

26:42.557 --> 26:43.776
GARRET [OS]:
Hi, good to see you.

26:43.819 --> 26:45.647
Good to see you. Well, just
dropped by, huh?

26:45.691 --> 26:47.170
GARRET [OS]:
Yeah, sorry I'm a little late.

26:47.214 --> 26:49.172
TIM [OS]:
Hey look who's here
everybody. Garret.

26:49.216 --> 26:50.783
Garret. You remember Garret for
God's sake!

26:50.826 --> 26:52.045
GARRET [OS]:
Hey, everyone.

26:52.088 --> 26:53.655
TIM [OS]:
Come on join us for
dinner.

26:53.699 --> 26:56.745
Garret, you remember, Valerie.
This is Valerie's friend Kazem.

26:56.789 --> 26:59.356
Fiance dad.

26:59.400 --> 27:00.183
Hello Kazem.

27:00.227 --> 27:02.751
It's Hazem.

27:05.711 --> 27:07.800
DETECTIVE HAVEN:
Was that the first time you met
Hazem Seif?

27:07.843 --> 27:09.192
GARRET:
I'd seen him before...

27:09.236 --> 27:11.281
but I hadn't officially met him
'till that night.

27:14.241 --> 27:16.025
What was your impression of him?

27:16.069 --> 27:17.984
I dunno.

27:18.027 --> 27:22.597
You dunno? You got five don't
you?

27:22.641 --> 27:23.511
What?

27:23.554 --> 27:25.208
Do you have five? You have five.

27:25.252 --> 27:26.383
Um.

27:26.427 --> 27:27.776
No, no, no, no. you stupid
little twerp.

27:27.820 --> 27:29.691
No, Five sens-

27:29.735 --> 27:32.389
Five senses. You know, Hearing,
taste, feeling.

27:32.433 --> 27:33.434
What?

27:33.477 --> 27:35.697
Hello! God gave you five
senses.

27:35.741 --> 27:37.046
Now what was your impression of
him?

27:37.090 --> 27:39.788
What was your opinion of Hazem
Seif?

27:39.832 --> 27:43.879
He was kinda rude I guess. It
was just..

27:43.923 --> 27:45.664
It was an awkward
night.

27:45.707 --> 27:47.622
TIM [OS]:
Kazem was just telling us about
living in Egypt.

27:47.666 --> 27:49.102
It's a very interesting place.

27:49.145 --> 27:50.712
Mom, can I speak to you for a
minute?

27:50.756 --> 27:52.671
Oh. Valerie sweetheart, not now.

27:52.714 --> 27:53.889
Garret, would you like something
to drink.

27:53.933 --> 27:54.760
Mom!

27:54.803 --> 27:58.415
Golly, alright. Excuse us.

28:02.202 --> 28:04.900
Mom what the hell is he doing
here?

28:04.944 --> 28:06.293
I bring my fiance to meet
you,

28:06.336 --> 28:08.904
And you invite my ex-boyfriend
on the same night?

28:08.948 --> 28:10.558
Valerie, I'm not in love with
your tone.

28:10.601 --> 28:11.777
I have chosen someone

28:11.820 --> 28:14.214
So your guys' little plan isn't
going to work.

28:14.257 --> 28:15.824
That's fine.

28:15.868 --> 28:18.392
Now let's go back to our guests
and enjoy a pleasant dinner.

28:18.435 --> 28:19.393
